                      Fashion with compassion                    Known to be a launching platform for young and upcoming designers, Nouveaau has carved an exclusive niche for itself over the years. It has steadily generated tremendous interest among the best designers in the industry, generating over 7,000 exclusive clientele all over the country and beyond. Hosted in association with t2, Nouveaau will showcase Indias leading designers display their creations from pret to couture, bridal saris, lehngas, Indo-Western, formal and semi-formal to kidswear. Over 65 designers, striking a balance between creativity and style, ethnic and western, chic and comfort, will participate. Those with a penchant for stylish accessories will be spoilt for choice by the amazing array of chunky, silver and silver-plated jewellery, jadau and chic footwear. Eclectic styles in gold patra and diamond jewellery will also vie for the attention of those with a taste for the ethnic. There will also be a wide range in home decor from table accessories, cushion covers, throws, runners, bed-linen and ceramic pots to choose from, besides the exclusive collection of art and paintings.         Kicking off this edition of Nouveaau is a fashion show with Poonam Bhagat - Taika (Delhi), Jyoti Jain - J Square (Delhi), Raj Shroff - Ravage (Hyderabad), Monisha Tharyamal (Jaipur), Yusuf Maklai - Cinderalla Shoes (Mumbai), Amrisha J and Ranu Khaitan - ICY (Calcutta) at Tantra tonight.        This fashion, lifestyle and art show also has a cause to support, as a part of its proceeds will go to Sisters of the Poor, Home for the Aged, Calcutta.                   Event: Fashion show (today; Tantra (The Park); 9 pm - 11 pm) Exhibition (July 17, Taj Bengal; 11 am - 8 pm)	                    
